definitions.definition: The act of counting or tallying a quantity.
examples: Give the chairs a quick count to check if we have enough.

definitions.definition: The result of a tally that reveals the number of items in a set; a quantity counted .
( law ) A distinct and separate charge in an indictment or complaint .
( baseball ) The number of balls and strikes , respectively, on a batter's in-progress plate appearance .
examples: He has a 3–2 count with the bases loaded.

definitions.definition: ( obsolete ) An object of interest or account; value; estimation.
( euphemistic , slang ) Cunt ( the taboo swear word )

definitions.definition: The male ruler of a county .
A nobleman holding a rank intermediate between dukes and barons .
Any of various nymphalid butterflies of the genus Tanaecia . Other butterflies in this genus are called earls and viscounts .
